{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"877f0219-8cc7-477f-a70f-c6a2b4b31db1","content":"Good — I can see the project: a minimal .NET 10 Web API with two small markdown docs and no dependencies yet. Here's the plan:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐       ┌────────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md   │──────▶│  Ingestion       │──────▶│  Vector Store  │\n│  (on disk)   │       │  Pipeline        │       │  (in-memory or │\n└──────────────┘       │  • Read files    │       │   persistent)  │\n                       │  • Chunk text    │       └───────┬────────┘\n                       │  • Embed chunks  │               │\n                       └──────────────────┘               │ similarity\n                                                          │ search\n┌──────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐               │\n│   Client     │──────▶│  POST /ask       │───────────────┘\n│   (HTTP)     │◀──────│  • Embed query   │\n└──────────────┘       │  • Retrieve top-K│       ┌────────────────┐\n                       │  • Build prompt  │──────▶│  LLM (OpenAI / │\n                       │  • Return answer │◀──────│  Azure OpenAI)  │\n                       └──────────────────┘       └────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n| Concern | Approach |\n|---|---|\n| **Embedding + LLM** | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` + `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` (first-party .NET abstractions; swap providers freely) |\n| **Vector store** | Start with the in-memory `JsonVectorStore` for dev; swap to Qdrant/Azure AI Search later via DI |\n| **Chunking** | Split each markdown file by heading (`# / ##`) then sliding-window (~500 tokens, 100-token overlap) |\n| **Embedding model** | `text-embedding-3-small` (via OpenAI or Azure OpenAI) |\n| **Chat model** | `gpt-4o-mini` (good cost/quality for grounded Q&A) |\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### 1 — Add NuGet packages\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` (embedding + chat)\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.Abstractions` + in-memory provider\n- `Markdig` (parse markdown structure for heading-aware chunking)\n\n### 2 — Define the data model\n- `DocumentChunk` record: `Id`, `SourceFile`, `Heading`, `Content`, `Vector`\n- Register a `VectorStoreCollection<string, DocumentChunk>` in DI.\n\n### 3 — Build the ingestion pipeline (`Services/IngestionService.cs`)\n1. Enumerate `Docs/*.md`.\n2. Parse each file → split into sections by heading.\n3. Apply sliding-window sub-chunking for sections exceeding token limit.\n4. Call the embedding generator for each chunk in batches.\n5. Upsert chunks into the vector store collection.\n6. Expose as `IHostedService` that runs on startup (+ a `POST /ingest` endpoint to re-trigger).\n\n### 4 — Build the query endpoint (`Controllers/AskController.cs`)\n- **`POST /ask`** — accepts `{ \"question\": \"...\" }`.\n  1. Embed the question.\n  2. Vector similarity search → top-5 chunks.\n  3. Build a system prompt: _\"Answer using only the provided context. Cite the source file.\"_\n  4. Send `[system + context + user question]` to the chat model.\n  5. Return `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [...] }`.\n\n### 5 — Configuration & DI wiring (`Program.cs`)\n- Read `OpenAI:ApiKey`, `OpenAI:EmbeddingModel`, `OpenAI:ChatModel` from `appsettings.json` / env vars.\n- Register `IChatClient`, `IEmbeddingGenerator`, vector store collection, `IngestionService`.\n\n### 6 — Validation & testing\n- Verify the build compiles against .NET 10.\n- Manually test with `curl` against both endpoints.\n- Confirm answers cite the correct source file.\n\n## Notes\n- **No external DB required** for the initial version — the in-memory store keeps things simple.  \n- **Swappability**: because `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` is provider-agnostic, switching to Azure OpenAI or a local model later is a config change, not a code change.  \n- The chunking strategy (heading-split + sliding window) suits small-to-medium doc sets well; for larger corpora, consider a dedicated document-intelligence step.\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c939d2ff-3f88-46bf-b072-370ce265ec0a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me create a plan for the RAG-based Q&A feature. The user explicitly said \"plan and architecture only — do not write any code.\"\n\nLet me create a plan.md in the session workspace.","outputTokens":1255},"id":"1cabe890-018b-4439-b075-8ef3810f03af","timestamp":"2026-04-08T02:22:23.528Z","parentId":"53a0293c-de98-4636-9de5-94bcc2ce1440"}
